<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8391127>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Micrographs of amphipod taxa encountered in Kuwait during this study. A: Ampithoe ramondi, male habitus; B: Cymadusa setosa, male habitus; C: Grandidierella gilesi, male habitus; D: Bemlos acuticoxa, male habitus; E: Globosolembos indicus, habitus of female with eggs; F: Cyproidea sp. cf. serratipalma, female habitus; G: Metaprotella macoranicus, female habitus; H: Leucothoe gracilis, male habitus; I: Ceradocus (Denticeradocus) alama, female habitus; J: Elasmopus alkhiranensis, male habitus; K: Dulichiella fresnelii, male habitus; L: Maera irregularis, female habitus; M: Melita persia, male habitus; N: Stenothoe gallensis, male habitus. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, F); 1 mm (C–E, H, N); 2 mm (B, G, I–M)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8391127/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

